headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 30 points and JaVale McGee added 20 in their Michigan homecomings to help the NBA-leading Phoenix Suns rout the Detroit Pistons 135-108 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, McGee help Suns rout Pistons in Michigan homecoming

headlines.description: — Christian Wood had 23 points and 14 rebounds, Eric Gordon made a clutch bucket with 12.5 seconds remaining and the Houston Rockets held off the Sacramento Kings 118-112 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon's late basket helps Rockets hold off Kings 118-112

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 26 points and 11 rebounds to lead the Minnesota Timberwolves to a 119-99 victory over the worn-out Golden State Warriors, who played without Steph Curry and Draymond Green on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns carries Timberwolves past Curry-less Warriors, 119-99

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 18 points and 19 rebounds in his return to Utah’s lineup, Donovan Mitchell scored 31 points and the Jazz beat the Denver Nuggets 125-102 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert has double-double, Jazz beat Nuggets 125-102
